<?xml version='1.0' encoding='ISO-8859-1' ?>
<grammar>
<section>
<title>Present simple: &lt;i&gt;he&lt;/i&gt;, &lt;i&gt;she&lt;/i&gt;,&lt;i&gt; it:&lt;/i&gt; positive </title>
<sectiontitle>In the positive, we use &lt;i&gt;he/she/it &lt;/i&gt;+ verb + -&lt;i&gt;s &lt;/i&gt;or&lt;i&gt; -es&lt;/i&gt;.</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>el_gram_4_1_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1>With verbs ending with a consonant (&lt;i&gt;b, d, f&lt;/i&gt; etc.) we add&lt;i&gt; -s.&lt;/i&gt;</text1>
<text1a>It &lt;b&gt;opens&lt;/b&gt; at 7 and &lt;b&gt;closes &lt;/b&gt;at 6.</text1a>
<sound1>el_gram_4_1_2.mp3</sound1>
<text2>With verbs ending with &lt;i&gt;o, ch, sh, s, x, z, &lt;/i&gt;we add&lt;i&gt; -es.&lt;/i&gt;</text2>
<text2a>Paolo &lt;b&gt;does&lt;/b&gt; his homework and then &lt;b&gt;watches&lt;/b&gt; TV.</text2a>
<sound2>el_gram_4_1_3.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2>With verbs ending with a consonant + &lt;i&gt;-y&lt;/i&gt;, we change this to -&lt;i&gt;ies&lt;/i&gt;.</sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>el_gram_4_1_4.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3>f&lt;b&gt;ly&lt;/b&gt; car&lt;b&gt;ry&lt;/b&gt; t&lt;b&gt;ry&lt;/b&gt; stu&lt;b&gt;dy&lt;/b&gt;</text3>
<text3a>When he &lt;b&gt;flies&lt;/b&gt; he always &lt;b&gt;carries&lt;/b&gt; a sports bag.</text3a>
<sound3>el_gram_4_1_5.mp3</sound3>
<text4>but &lt;FONT COLOR='#FC214C'&gt;NOT&lt;/FONT&gt; with &lt;i&gt;stay&lt;/i&gt; or &lt;i&gt;play&lt;/i&gt;</text4>
<text4a>She always &lt;b&gt;stays&lt;/b&gt; with her grandmother.</text4a>
<sound4>el_gram_4_1_6.mp3</sound4>
</section>
<section>
<title>Like + &lt;i&gt;-ing &lt;/i&gt;</title>
<sectiontitle>We use &lt;i&gt;like/love/hate &lt;/i&gt;+ verb + -&lt;i&gt;ing.&lt;/i&gt;</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>el_gram_4_1_7.mp3</titlesound>
<text1></text1>
<text1a>He &lt;b&gt;hates cooking&lt;/b&gt;.</text1a>
<sound1>el_gram_4_1_8.mp3</sound1>
<text2></text2>
<text2a>I &lt;b&gt;don't like swimming&lt;/b&gt;.</text2a>
<sound2>el_gram_4_1_9.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2></sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2></titlesound2>
<text3></text3>
<text4></text4>
<text4a></text4a>
<sound4></sound4>
</section>
</grammar>